def data_info(title, data):
    print('  "{}":'.format(title))
    print()
    
    data.info()
    
    print()
    print()
    
    print('  ( 5 ):')
    display(data.sample(5, random_state=r_state))

    print()
    print()
    
    print('   :')
    print()
    for col in data.columns:
        nmv = data[col].isna().sum()
        pmv = nmv/len(data)
        
        if pmv == 0:
            print('\033[0m{} - {} . - {:.2%}'.format(col, nmv, pmv))
        elif pmv <= 0.1:
            print('\033[0m{} - \033[43m{} .\033[0m - \033[43m{:.2%}'.format(col, nmv, pmv))
        else:
            print('\033[0m{} - \033[41m{} .\033[0m - \033[41m{:.2%}'.format(col, nmv, pmv))
        print('\033[0m')
    
    print()
    
    print('    :')
    print()
    for col in data.columns:
        print('{} - {}'.format(col, data[col].nunique()))
        
    print()
    print()
    
    print('  : {} .'.format(data.duplicated().sum()))

def corr_info(data, col_del):
    print(' :')
    print()
    corr_matrix = data.drop(columns=col_del).corr()
    sns.set(font_scale=1.15)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
    sns.heatmap(
                corr_matrix,        
                cmap='RdBu_r',
                annot=True,
                vmin=-1, vmax=1);
    plt.show()
    print()
    for i in range(len(corr_matrix.columns)):
        for j in range(i):
            cor = corr_matrix.iloc[i, j]
            print('  {}  {}:'.format(corr_matrix.columns[i], corr_matrix.columns[j]))
            if cor == 0:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n  ')
            elif 0 < cor <= 0.3:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            elif -0.3 <= cor < 0:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            elif 0.3 < cor <= 0.7:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            elif -0.7 <= cor < -0.3:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            elif 0.7 < cor < 1:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            elif -1 < cor < -0.7:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            elif cor == 1:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            elif cor == -1:
                print(f' : {cor:.6f} \n   ')
            else:
                print('  ')
            print()

#     

def split_data(data, target, test_size):
    features = data.drop([target] , axis=1)
    target = data[target]

    features_train, features_test, target_train, target_test = train_test_split(
    features, target, test_size=test_size, random_state=r_state)
    
    features_list = {'features_train' : features_train, 'features_test' : features_test}
    targets_list = {'target_train' : target_train, 'target_test' : target_test}

    print(' :')
    print()
    for i in features_list:
        sh = features_list[i].shape
        psh = sh[0]/len(data)
        print('{} - : {} ., : {} . - {:.2%}'.format(i, sh[0], sh[1], psh))
    
    print()

    print(' :')
    print()
    for i in targets_list:
        sh = targets_list[i].shape
        psh = sh[0]/len(data)
        print('{} - : {} . - {:.2%}'.format(i, sh[0], psh))
    
    return features_train, features_test, target_train, target_test

Умножение матриц¶

:

  • $X$ ( )

  • $y$

  • $P$ ,

  • $w$ ( )

:

$$ a = Xw $$

:

$$ w = \arg\min_w MSE(Xw, y) $$

:

$$ w = (X^T X)^{-1} X^T y $$

:

$a = a_1$

  1. $X_1$ $X$ $P$:
$$ X_1 = X P $$
  1. $X_1$ $w_1$:
$$ w_1 = ((X P)^T X P)^{-1} (X P)^T y $$
  1. $(XP)^T$:
$$ w_1 = (X^T P^T X P)^{-1} X^T P^T y $$
  1. $(X^T P^T X P)^{-1}$:
$$ w_1 = ((X^T X) (P^T P))^{-1} X^T P^T y $$
  1. $((X^T X) (P^T P))^{-1}$:
$$ w_1 = (X^T X)^{-1} (P^T P)^{-1} X^T P^T y = P^{-1} (X^T X)^{-1} (P^T)^{-1} P^T X^T y $$
  1. $P$ - $\Rightarrow$ $(P^T)^{-1} P^T = E$, $E$ - :
$$ w_1 = P^{-1} (X^T X)^{-1} E X^T y = P^{-1} (X^T X)^{-1} X^T y $$
  1. $(X^T X)^{-1} X^T y$ $w$:
$$ w_1 = P^{-1} w $$
  1. $w_1$ $a = Xw$:
$$ a_1 = X_1 w_1 = X P P^{-1} w $$
  1. $P$ - $\Rightarrow$ $P P^{-1} = E$, $E$ - :
$$ a_1 = X_1 w_1 = X P P^{-1} w = X E w = X w = a $$

, $a_1$ $X$, $P$, $a$

:

$X$ $P$

$w$ $w_1$ :

$$ w_1 = P^{-1} w $$
